  "summary": "The Japan Export-Import Bank (日本輸出入銀行 / JEXIM) was Japan's principal state export-credit and overseas-investment lending institution from 1950 to 1999. In 1999 it merged with the Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund (海外経済協力基金 / OECF) to form the original Japan Bank for International Cooperation (JBIC)",
